# Internationalization (i18n) Patterns

## Project Requirements
TREND supports English (EN) and Bulgarian (BG) languages with localStorage persistence.

## Translation Data Structure

Store translations in structured objects:

```js
export const servicesTranslations = {
  haircuts: {
    en: "Haircuts & Styling",
    bg: "Подстригване и прически"
  },
  coloring: {
    en: "Coloring",
    bg: "Боядисване"
  },
  treatments: {
    en: "Hair Treatments",
    bg: "Терапии за коса"
  }
}
```

## Translation Hook Pattern

```jsx
export const useTranslation = () => {
  const [lang, setLang] = useState(() => 
    localStorage.getItem('trendLang') || 'en'
  )
  
  const t = (translations) => {
    return translations[lang] || translations.en
  }
  
  const changeLanguage = (newLang) => {
    setLang(newLang)
    localStorage.setItem('trendLang', newLang)
    document.documentElement.lang = newLang
  }
  
  return { lang, t, changeLanguage }
}
```

## Usage in Components

```jsx
import { useTranslation } from '../hooks/useTranslation'

export const ServiceCard = ({ service }) => {
  const { t } = useTranslation()
  
  return (
    <div className="service-card">
      <h3>{t(service.name)}</h3>
      <p>{t(service.description)}</p>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Language Context Pattern

For app-wide language state:

```jsx
import { createContext, useContext, useState } from 'react'

const LanguageContext = createContext()

export const LanguageProvider = ({ children }) => {
  const [lang, setLang] = useState(() => 
    localStorage.getItem('trendLang') || 'en'
  )
  
  const changeLanguage = (newLang) => {
    setLang(newLang)
    localStorage.setItem('trendLang', newLang)
    document.documentElement.lang = newLang
  }
  
  return (
    <LanguageContext.Provider value={{ lang, changeLanguage }}>
      {children}
    </LanguageContext.Provider>
  )
}

export const useLanguage = () => useContext(LanguageContext)
```

## Language Switcher Component

```jsx
export const LanguageToggle = () => {
  const { lang, changeLanguage } = useLanguage()
  
  return (
    <div className="lang-toggle">
      <button 
        className={lang === 'en' ? 'active' : ''}
        onClick={() => changeLanguage('en')}
      >
        EN
      </button>
      <span className="divider">|</span>
      <button 
        className={lang === 'bg' ? 'active' : ''}
        onClick={() => changeLanguage('bg')}
      >
        BG
      </button>
    </div>
  )
}
```

